Title: Should you fine tune for JSON output?
Description: JSON Schemas are a great format to structure outputs of LLMs. Their spec gives you wide latitude in specifying expected constraints (length, enum values, nested objects). Coupled with logit masking, schemas allow you to guarantee the format of your output so there's no fiddling with unexpected values. It turns LLMs into building blocks with a clear API and makes them a lot more modular.

Title: How I fall asleep February 21, 2024 on Sepi's blog
